{{Han etyl}}
{{liushu|p}} – an image of a baby, with a large head and spread arms. The legs are wrapped in a blanket. Compare with {{zh-l|*了}}, where the arms are wrapped.

The big seal script form is much more elaborate, showing a baby with hair on a head ({{zh-l|*囟}}) and arms on the two sides of the body, sitting on a stool ({{zh-l|*几}}).

